~~~~~~~~~No. This is a funny thing to me.  I hear about so many=20
people being super scared to give out their SS#.  Well folks,=20
I can get your SS# for 50 cents.  Give me a name and address=20
and about 90% of the time I can get the number.  We are so worried about putt=
ing our credit card number on
the net, but we will give the card to a waiter or waitress and=20
they take it out of our sight for 10 minutes.  They could do=20
who knows what with the CC number.  I once had a person=20
tell me that her lawyer said that she should never fax a copy=20
of her check to anyone (checks by fax) because then that=20
person (me) would have her account info and could write=20
a check out for thousands of dollars.  I told her to just send=20
it to me then and she said that was OK.  Then I asked her=20
to tell me what the difference was between the original check=20
and a fax copy.  I told her to ask her lawyer that too.  Never=20
heard back from her.  The bottom line is that if a crook wants to get your in=
fo, it is=20
available in many places.  Have a good day.
--  Terry    http://mysiteinc.com/tfn/lfi.html
~~~~~~~~~Yes. I believe that the risk is out there but minimal. However,=20
we can cut those risks by a few simple precautions. Most=20
importantly, never give any personal information at a site=20
that is not secure, always look for the lock in thetask bar=20
or a Veri secure sign or others. Also, never leave your information stored at=
 a site. I put=20
in my credit information in each time instead of having=20
an account in standing, a little more time but less risks=20
involved! Of course, I mostly shop at my own Internet=20
mall and I know how safe it is there, credit card info is=20
deleted in a matter of seconds. Overall, I believe the web=20
to be a safe and very fruitful new frontier!
--  Catherine F.      http://www.catco.nexgenmall.com=20
~~~~~~~~~Yes. I had phenomena for 6 weeks and did not realize that=20
my ISP was shut down at the same time because the owner=20
was in a bad car accident.  I had a full service account. =20
My Internic fees were not paid so my WEB Address=20
went unprotected.  A Russian stepped in; paid the fees;=20
and, promptly assigned my www.SchoolOfGeomatics.com=20
address to a porn shop.  Thus, I lost 4 years of building=20
up 1st place rankings on 12 Search Engines and 2nd place=20
on 8 more.  This set me back about 4  months: I believe I=20
lost a minimum of $50,000. =20
=20
I have also been hit with viruses about 10 times.  The first=20
time I lost almost 4 months of work.  Now, I back up often=20
enough to not to lose so much time.  This is also Internet=20
theft.  These people are nothing but out and out criminals=20
and should spend years behind bars.
=20
Customers are well protected from credit card theft;=20
however, merchants can lose a lot of money.  I sell only by=20
purchase order and certified or registered company checks.
